<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n53116i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53116i">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53116i"> 116(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Carleton Wm. <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n53116i"> <li>FW unlocated</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources"><mark>CARLETON, WILLIAM</mark>, novelist; b. Prillisk, Tyrone, 1794; d. Dublin, 1869; his father was a small farmer, a mine of legends and folk lore, and his mother a beautiful singer of old songs; intended for priesthood; came under protestant influence and converted; wrote short stories founded mainly on personal experience and tales by his father; these <cite>Traits and Stories</cite>, published in 1830, became immensely popular; thenceforth he depended on his pen, from which a long series of novels, of varying merit, proceeded; received civil list pension of &pound;200 per annum. <small> John S. Crone, <a name="JSCD1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JSCD1"><cite title="source">A Concise Dictionary of Irish Biography</cite></a> (Apr 1928) 29</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
